4 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
5 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
6 Article – Land Use
7 1–401.
8 (a) Except as provided in this section, this division does not apply to charter
9 counties.
10 (b) The following provisions of this division apply to a charter county:
11 (19) § 4–217 (PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE);
12 [(19)] (20) Title 4, Subtitle 5 (Accessory Dwelling Units);
13 [(20)] (21) § 5–102(d) (Subdivision regulations – Burial sites);
14 [(21)] (22) § 5–104 (Major subdivision – Review);
15 [(22)] (23) Title 7, Subtitle 1 (Development Mechanisms);
16 [(23)] (24) Title 7, Subtitle 2 (Transfer of Development Rights);
17 [(24)] (25) except in Montgomery County or Prince George’s County, Title
18 7, Subtitle 3 (Development Rights and Responsibilities Agreements);
19 [(25)] (26) Title 7, Subtitle 4 (Inclusionary Zoning);
20 [(26)] (27) Title 7, Subtitle 5 (Housing Expansion and Affordability);
21 [(27)] (28) § 8–401 (Conversion of overhead facilities);
22 [(28)] (29) for Baltimore County only, Title 9, Subtitle 3 (Single–County
23 Provisions – Baltimore County);
24 [(29)] (30) for Frederick County only, Title 9, Subtitle 10 (Single–County
