HOUSE BILL 1267 3
1 [(31)] (32) for Talbot County only, Title 9, Subtitle 18 (Single–County
2 Provisions – Talbot County); and
3 [(32)] (33) Title 11, Subtitle 2 (Civil Penalty).
4 4–217.
5 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
6 INDICATED.
7 (2) “DISTRICT COUNCIL” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 14–101 OF
8 THIS ARTICLE.
9 (3) “LOCAL ZONING AUTHORITY” MEANS:
10 (I) A LOCAL JURISDICTION; OR
11 (II) FOR PROPERTY LOCATED IN THE
12 MARYLAND–WASHINGTON REGIONAL DISTRICT ESTABLISHED UNDER TITLE 20,
13 SUBTITLE 1 OF THIS ARTICLE, A DISTRICT COUNCIL.
14 (B) ANY FEDERALLY OWNED LAND THAT IS PART OF THE PROPERTY KNOWN
15 AS THE PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE SHALL BE DESIGNATED AND MAINTAINED IN
16 A ZONING CLASSIFICATION THAT RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE, RESERVED
17 OPEN SPACE, OR OTHER RESOURCE CONSERVATION USES.
18 (C) IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OR ANY ASSIGNEE SELLS, LEASES,
19 LICENSES, OR OTHERWISE ENCUMBERS ANY PORTION OF LAND THAT IS PART OF THE
20 PROPERTY KNOWN AS THE PATUXENT RESEARCH REFUGE, THE LOCAL ZONING
21 AUTHORITY SHALL CONTINUE A ZONING CLASSIFICATION FOR THAT PROPERTY
22 THAT:
23 (1) RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE, RESERVED OPEN SPACE,
24 OR OTHER RESOURCE CONSERVATION USES; AND
25 (2) DOES NOT PERMIT COMMERCIAL, INDUSTRIAL, OR RESIDENTIAL
26 USES.
27 [25–211.
28 If the United States Department of Agriculture sells any portion of the property
29 known as the Beltsville Agricultural Research Center, the district council shall place and
30 permanently maintain the land in a zoning classification of agricultural open space
31 immediately after the transfer of the land to the buyer.]

4 HOUSE BILL 1267
1 25–211.
2 (A) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, THE DISTRICT COUNCIL
3 SHALL DESIGNATE AND MAINTAIN THE FEDERALLY OWNED PROPERTY KNOWN AS
4 THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER OR ANY OTHER U.S.
5 DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE PROPERTY IN BELTSVILLE OR ITS VICINITY TO A
6 ZONING CLASSIFICATION THAT RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE OR RESERVED
7 OPEN SPACE.
8 (B) IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OR ANY ASSIGNEE SELLS, LEASES,
9 LICENSES, OR OTHERWISE ENCUMBERS ANY PORTION OF THE PROPERTY KNOWN AS
10 THE BELTSVILLE AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH CENTER OR ANY OTHER U.S.
11 DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE PROPERTY IN BELTSVILLE OR ITS VICINITY, THE
12 DISTRICT COUNCIL SHALL CONTINUE A ZONING CLASSIFICATION FOR THAT
13 PROPERTY THAT RESTRICTS THE USES TO OPEN SPACE OR RESERVED OPEN SPACE.
14 (C) THE DISTRICT COUNCIL MAY NOT APPROVE ANY OVERLAYS, SPECIAL
15 EXCEPTIONS, OR MODIFICATIONS TO THE ZONING CLASSIFICATIONS REQUIRED BY
16 THIS SECTION.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
18 1, 2026.

